  "elapsed_s": 2.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This is as far as I-- it's a little nebulous, but this, I could grasp at the time, that there was kind of movement to move out, to move away.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The fact is that at a later point, my father, God bless his soul, tried to escape to France, but France was conquered before it could materialize, and my father, as I mentioned before, ended up in Dachau, where he died and-- was murdered-- in 1940-- oh, no, 1941.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And generally, I have in the writings I have all these days accurate, so please forgive me if I'm not very accurate now because I try to dwell on the story rather.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But his first concentration camp was Oranienburg and from there, as I read it from documents, and I read it from documents which were made at that time by the [INAUDIBLE] in Leipzig, he was transferred to Dachau, and further source was a-- a telegram or a letter from the what we call [INAUDIBLE] that-- that they told us this-- this story.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, at that time, it was my grandmother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was a widow, and I was the grandchild who carries the name of my grandfather from her side.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was that she had her own apartment, but at a later point, we lived together, my grandmother, my aunt, Mary, my other aunt, [?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Lana, ?] my uncle, Max, because we-- the circumstances under the Nazis forced us to live in much more crowded conditions.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The fact is that my grandmother had in Leipzig at the time my grandfather died two houses, but the economic situation had then already deteriorated because there was some element of racial problem at that time before Hitler.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so she had to sell the houses, and they had to survive.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
